Master video generation with expert-level prompting techniques using Googleâ€™s Veo 3

Introduction
Veo 3 is Googleâ€™s most advanced Artificial Intelligence (AI) video generation model to date. It creates high-quality videos from text or images and can even generate synchronized audio from a single prompt. As one of the most powerful generative video models available today, Veo 3 unlocks new creative possibilities for filmmakers, marketers, and content creators.

Creating compelling videos with generative AI requires thoughtful prompting. This requires a different approach than prompting a large language model.

In this guide:

We share experimentation-based prompting guidance for Veo 3.
You will learn how to structure effective prompts for Veo 3, apply best practices for video generation and avoid common pitfalls even without prior experience in AI or video production.
The Anatomy of a Veo 3 Prompt
Creating a great Veo 3 prompt is different from prompting a chatbot. Itâ€™s about using the right terminology and prompt structure. Breaking your creative idea down into key components is the most effective way to guide Veo 3 toward your desired outcome.

Figure 1, below, illustrates this structure, outlining the nine core elements of an expert-level prompt. These elements represent the key building blocks you may use when crafting your prompt. However, itâ€™s important to note that you donâ€™t need to include all of them in every prompt. The right combination depends on your specific goals.

